National Security Advisor Susan E. Rice issued a statement expressing hope for the peace agreement signed by South Sudan President Salva Kiir and Riek Machar. The agreement, signed in Addis Ababa, Ethiopia, aims to end the ongoing crisis and bring peace and prosperity to the people of South Sudan. Rice commended the Intergovernmental Authority on Development (IGAD) for facilitating the talks and urged both parties to honor the agreement by ending violence and negotiating in good faith for a political agreement that ensures stability, prosperity, and peace for all of South Sudan's people.